s solid, but I want to be careful and thorough in my process!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Organizing files**\\\\n\\\\nI need to make sure the file package is consistent, using public classes without the dollar sign. I think creating two files is the way to go here. I could use bash to create the directories, but it seems unnecessary, so Iā€™ll focus on writing the new files instead. If I need to remove any files later, Iā€™ll use the rm command. This all feels pretty straightforward!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_0Q5bQPRxaH1Z49fDpXGJQGYb|fc_002e273752b5cc99016a1133a403508194817dde27d451b5b6\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-nio/4.0.24/src/test/groovy/org_apache_groovy/groovy_nio/NioExtensionsTest.groovy\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_groovy.groovy_nio\\n\\nimport groovy.io.FileType\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir\\n\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\n\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertArrayEquals\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame\\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue\\n\\npublic class NioExtensionsTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void readsWritesAndTransformsTextUsingPathExtensionMethods(@TempDir Path tempDir) {\\n        Path file = tempDir.resolve('sample.txt')\\n\\n        file.text = 'alpha\\\\nbeta\\\\ngamma\\\\n'\\n\\n        assertEquals('alpha\\\\nbeta\\\\ngamma\\\\n', file.text)\\n        assertEquals(['alpha', 'beta', 'gamma'], file.readLines())\\n        assertEquals(17L, file.size())\\